io.craigmiller160.school.repo

Class HibernateScJoinHolderDao

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.craigmiller160.school.repo.HibernateScJoinHolderDao
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GenericEntityDao<ScJoinHolder>, GenericJoinHolderDao<ScJoinHolder>, GenericJoinHolderDaoBean<ScJoinHolder>, GenericPaginatedEntityDao<ScJoinHolder>, GenericPaginatedJoinHolderDao<ScJoinHolder>

    @Component(value="scJoinHolderDao")
public class HibernateScJoinHolderDao
extends java.lang.Object
implements GenericJoinHolderDaoBean<ScJoinHolder>
    A DAO class for using the Hibernate framework to persist ScJoinHolder entities. This class depends on a Hibernate SessionFactory to generate the database sessions and connections. This class does NOT manage its own transactions, it will depend on a service layer class to handle that functionality.

    THREAD SAFETY: This class is thread-safe. It has no mutable state that could cause issues with multiple threads.

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    craig

                                                             int entityId,
                                                             int startPageAfterRow,
                                                             int pageRowCount)
        Get a "page" of JoinHolder entities from the database that joined with the entity whose type and unique ID are specified in the parameters. A page is essentially a sub-list of records from the database. The size of a page is defined by the fourth parameter (pageRowCount). The offset is determined by the third parameter (startPageAfterRow).
        Specified by:
        getEntitiesByPageFor in interface GenericPaginatedJoinHolderDao<ScJoinHolder>
        Type Parameters:
        U - the type of entity that is joined.
        Parameters:
        joinedEntityType - the type of entity to retrieve a "page" of its joined entities for.
        entityId - the unique ID of the entity to retrieve a "page" of its joined entities for.
        startPageAfterRow - the row in the table to start retrieving records after (eg. if this argument is 10, this method will retrieve records starting with row 11).
        pageRowCount - the total number of rows for the page (the total number of records to be retrieved).
        Returns:
        a sub-list of entities from the table that is a "page" of data, based on the supplied parameters.
